                "name": "Yury Shatz",
                "href": "/profile/Yury-Shatz"
            },
            "answer_text": "No, most of us don't. There's probably a small minority that does. This is our country, and we want it to be better - sure, we want better economy and medicine and roads like everyone, but we also want better ethnic policy and better relations with Russia and more thoghtful foreign policy in general. We are critical of our country but it does not mean we don't want it to exist.  Think of us as opposition. There are americans that are anti-Republican and anti-Democrat and some of them anti-establishment. There are americans that think their country is deeply screwed up. But they don't want US to be part of another country. It's insulting when we are forced to prove our loyalty. ",
