                "name": "Mindaugas Kubilius",
                "href": "/profile/Mindaugas-Kubilius"
            },
            "answer_text": "Living in Vilnius, Lithuania I know many local Russian people, some of them very closely, and must say that nobody, not a single soul have expressed a slightest sentiment of joining Russia under any circumstances. Some people can be pro Putin, some anti Putin. Actually the fiercest criticisms of Russian official politics I have heard was from my fellow Russians. There are some strongly supporting Russian patriotism. But when it comes to practical matters like choosing where to live I think people here are well determined. There is a very good point in other answers that it is a serious insult for Russian people if they are forced to prove their loyalty to the country they are born into and live there. I would never ever challenge anybody with such a request. ",
