        {
            "author_info": {
                "name": "Indrek P\u00e4rli",
                "href": "/profile/Indrek-P\u00e4rli"
            },
            "answer_text": "My subjective opinion as a native Estonian. It's my personal understanding that large part of ethnic Russians in Estonia consider such question as an insult and I think they are right. They may speak a different language, but most of them are born and raised here, Estonia is their homeland, not Russia. They may have a different opinion about Putin and situation in Ukraine, but they have little or no interest of Baltics to join Russia.  I think some of them have grown patriotic feelings towards the country they live in, for some it's just pragmatic calculation - life quality is higher in Baltics than in Russia.   Recently, I found a question from Quora What does it feel to be an ethnic Russian in the Baltic states? and I recommend an answer there from ethnic Russian in Estonia . Good insight. ",
